{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold tour operators accountable for the safety of accommodation provided",
        "additional_details": "I think the government should address this issue because travellers trust tour operators to provide safe, quality accommodations. When this trust is broken, it puts people\u2019s health and well-being at risk. I think that clear regulations and enforcement are needed to ensure tour operators thoroughly vet the places they promote. Without government action, I think unsafe practices could continue, which could leave customers vulnerable. I think accountability must be a legal obligation.",
        "background": "I want there to be a new law that specifically holds tour operators responsible for the health and safety of accommodations they promote. I think that customers may end up in unsafe conditions. I believe the Government should ensure clear standards and consequences for neglecting this responsibility",
